      "code": "2.40(b)(4)",
      "kind": "Critical",
      "repeat": false,
      "desc": "Attending veterinarian and adequate veterinary care (dealers and exhibitors).",
      "narrative": "On 12/23/2025 facility personnel were not given adequate guidance on the care of animals regarding handling and\nanesthesia of two wallabies. On 12/23/2025 a male wallaby (Bucky) and a Female wallaby (Eloise) were anesthetized for\nroutine veterinary medical examination procedures. At the time of this procedure both wallabies were given a vitamin E\nand selenium combination product as a prevention for capture myopathy. Bucky was administered selenium at a dosage\nof 0.84 mg/kg. Eloise was administered selenium at a dosage of 0.83 mg/kg. Before administration of the selenium\ncontaining product, a staff veterinarian verified that the calculated dosage to be administered was correct. However,\naccording to facility protocol the dosage that should have been administered was 0.076 mg/kg for Bucky and 0.076 mg/kg\nfor Eloise. The two wallabies died on 12/24/2025. Liver samples taken post-mortem and tested for selenium showed\nconcentrations of 16.42 ug/g for Bucky and 16.05 ug/g for Elosie. The cause of the two wallabies\u2019 death was determined\nto be selenium toxicosis.\nThe administration of proper dosages of medication is important to the health and well-being of the animals being cared\nfor.\nEach exhibitor shall establish and maintain programs of adequate veterinary care that include adequate guidance to\npersonnel involved in the care and use of animals regarding handling, immobilization, anesthesia, analgesia,\ntranquilization, and euthanasia.\nTo be corrected from this day (1/23/2026) forward.\nThis inspection and exit interview were conducted with facility representatives.\nn"
    }
  ],
  "narrative": "2.40(b)(4)  Critical\n   \nAttending veterinarian and adequate veterinary care (dealers and exhibitors). \nOn 12/23/2025 facility personnel were not given adequate guidance on the care of animals regarding handling and \nanesthesia of two wallabies. On 12/23/2025 a male wallaby (Bucky) and a Female wallaby (Eloise) were anesthetized for \nroutine veterinary medical examination procedures. At the time of this procedure both wallabies were given a vitamin E \nand selenium combination product as a prevention for capture myopathy. Bucky was administered selenium at a dosage \nof 0.84 mg/kg. Eloise was administered selenium at a dosage of 0.83 mg/kg. Before administration of the selenium \ncontaining product, a staff veterinarian verified that the calculated dosage to be administered was correct. However, \naccording to facility protocol the dosage that should have been administered was 0.076 mg/kg for Bucky and 0.076 mg/kg \nfor Eloise. The two wallabies died on 12/24/2025. Liver samples taken post-mortem and tested for selenium showed \nconcentrations of 16.42 ug/g for Bucky and 16.05 ug/g for Elosie. The cause of the two wallabies\u2019 death was determined \nto be selenium toxicosis. \n \nThe administration of proper dosages of medication is important to the health and well-being of the animals being cared \nfor. \n \nEach exhibitor shall establish and maintain programs of adequate veterinary care that include adequate guidance to \npersonnel involved in the care and use of animals regarding handling, immobilization, anesthesia, analgesia, \ntranquilization, and euthanasia. \n \nTo be corrected from this day (1/23/2026) forward. \n \nThis inspection and exit interview were conducted with facility representatives. \n \n n",
